        <p><strong>FoxPro</strong> is a text-based procedurally oriented programming language and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DBMS', 'DB'); ?>) originally published by <strong>Fox Software</strong> and later by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>) for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MS-DOS', 'DOS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Macintosh', 'ITH'); ?>, and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('UNIX', 'OS'); ?>.</p>
        <p>The final published release of FoxPro was 2.6.</p>
        <p>Development has continued under the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Visual FoxPro', 'L'); ?> label, which in turn was discontinued in 2007.</p>
        <p>Although FoxPro is a Database Management System (DBMS) and it does support relationships between tables, it is not considered a Relational Database Management System (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('RDBMS', 'DB'); ?>), lacking transactional processing.</p>
